![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/97fd6f9f-3d94-48cc-95e0-d973f48985db/20240408_181204.jpg)

In an electrifying announcement, WWE has revealed that the much-anticipated WWE Draft is scheduled to take place during the April 26th episode of SmackDown and the April 29th edition of WWE RAW. Wrestling fans around the globe are eagerly awaiting this event, as it promises to shake up the entire wrestling landscape.

Ilja Dragunov is the very first WWE Superstar declared for the Draft.

The WWE Draft has always been a pivotal moment in the wrestling calendar, where superstars from both SmackDown and RAW are selected to either stay on their current brand or move to the opposing show. This year, the draft comes with added excitement and intrigue, as Triple H has taken over complete creative control of the company.

With the recent surge in talent and the emergence of new stars, the WWE Draft couldn't come at a better time. Wrestlers across both brands have been making waves with their performances, and the draft provides an opportunity for fresh rivalries and storylines to unfold.

Additionally, the draft often serves as a platform for surprise returns and debuts, adding an element of unpredictability to the proceedings. Fans can expect twists and turns as their favorite superstars navigate the draft process, with alliances shifting and new dynamics forming.

As the wrestling world gears up for the WWE Draft, anticipation is reaching fever pitch. With just days to go until the draft kicks off on SmackDown, speculation is rife about who will be drafted where and what implications it will have for the future of WWE. One thing is for certain: the WWE Draft is sure to deliver excitement, drama, and unforgettable moments for fans worldwide.